title: Usage
text: input ggoncoplot data.frame 1 row per mutation. data.frame must contain columns describing following: Gene Symbol Sample Identifier (optional) mutation type (optional) tooltip (character string: show mouse hover particular mutation) columns can order, named anything. define mapping input dataset columns required features call ggoncoplot

title: Usage
code: # TCGA GBM dataset from TCGAmuations package gbm_csv <- system.file(package='ggoncoplot', "testdata/GBM_tcgamutations_mc3_maf.csv.gz") gbm_df <- read.csv(file = gbm_csv, header=TRUE)  gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode'   )

title: Usage
text: Colour mutation specifying col_mutation_type
code: # TCGA GBM dataset from TCGAmuations package gbm_csv <- system.file(package='ggoncoplot', "testdata/GBM_tcgamutations_mc3_maf.csv.gz") gbm_df <- read.csv(file = gbm_csv, header=TRUE)  gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification'   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: Show 4 frequently mutated genes using topn argument
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      topn = 4   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: Use genes_to_ignore argument filter specific genes, TTN MUC16. can use packages like somaticflags get lists genes might want filter .
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      topn = 10,     genes_to_ignore = c("TTN", "MUC16")   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 9 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/9 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 9/9 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: lets show TP53 TERT
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      genes_to_include = c('TP53', 'TERT'),   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 6 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/6 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 6/6 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: show_all_samples argument add samples don’t mutations selected genes plot. Note supply metadata table, default samples lacking mutations still shown. can include samples setting metadata_require_mutations = FALSE isn’t recommended unless ’re sure sample truly mutations dataframe.
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      show_all_samples = TRUE   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text:
Use col_tooltip argument indicate column input dataframe used custom tooltip. Note tooltips html, want insert break, just paste
. Similarly, want make text tooltip bold, try "text_to_bold<\b>". Note single sample multiple mutations gene, represented one tile oncoplot, tooltip mutation shown (newline delimited).
code: gbm_df |>    mutate(tooltip = paste0(Chromosome, ":", Start_Position, " ", Reference_Allele, ">", Tumor_Seq_Allele2)) |>   ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',      col_tooltip = 'tooltip' # We'll specify a custom tooltip based on our new 'tooltip' column   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

title: Usage
text: many samples mutations Gene (optionally coloured mutation type)
code: gbm_df |>    ggoncoplot(     col_genes = 'Hugo_Symbol',      col_samples = 'Tumor_Sample_Barcode',      col_mutation_type = 'Variant_Classification',     draw_gene_barplot = TRUE   ) #>  #> ── Identify Class ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #> ℹ Found 7 unique mutation types in input set #> ℹ 0/7 mutation types were valid SO terms #> ℹ 7/7 mutation types were valid MAF terms #> ✔ Mutation Types are described using valid MAF terms ... using MAF palete

text: many mutations (total) sample implemented yet: coming soon (https://github.com/selkamand/ggoncoplot/issues/30)

title: GG oncoplot — ggoncoplot
code: ggoncoplot(   .data,   col_genes,   col_samples,   col_mutation_type = NULL,   genes_to_include = NULL,   genes_to_ignore = NULL,   col_tooltip = col_samples,   topn = 10,   return_extra_genes_if_tied = FALSE,   palette = NULL,   metadata = NULL,   col_samples_metadata = col_samples,   metadata_require_mutations = TRUE,   show_sample_ids = FALSE,   interactive = TRUE,   interactive_svg_width = 12,   interactive_svg_height = 6,   xlab_title = "Sample",   ylab_title = "Gene",   fontsize_xlab = 26,   fontsize_ylab = 26,   fontsize_genes = 16,   fontsize_samples = 12,   fontsize_count = 14,   tile_height = 1,   tile_width = 1,   colour_backround = "grey90",   draw_gene_barplot = FALSE,   draw_tmb_barplot = FALSE,   show_all_samples = FALSE,   verbose = TRUE )

title: GG oncoplot — ggoncoplot
text: .data data oncoplot. data.frame 1 row per mutation cohort. Must contain columns describing gene_symbols sample_identifiers (data.frame) col_genes name data column containing gene names/symbols (string) col_samples name data column containing sample identifiers (string) col_mutation_type name data column describing mutation types (string) genes_to_include specific genes include oncoplot (character) genes_to_ignore names genes ignored (character) col_tooltip name data column containing whatever information want display (string) topn many top genes visualise. Ignored genes_to_include supplied (number) return_extra_genes_if_tied instead strictly returning topn genes, case ties (multiple genes mutated exact number samples, complicating selection top n genes), return tied genes (potentially topn). FALSE, return strictly topn genes, breaking ties based order appearance dataset (flag) palette named vector mapping possible mutation types (vector names) colours (vector values). supplied ggoncoplot check values either valid MAF variant classification terms use pre-made colour schemes ontologies mutationtypes package. mutation type terms described using ontologies, 12 colour RColourBrewer palette used, user warned make custom mapping force consistent colour schemes plots (character) metadata dataframe describing sample level metadata. One column must contain unique sample identifiers. columns can describe numeric / categorical metadata (data.frame) col_samples_metadata column metadata data.frame describes sample identifiers (string) metadata_require_mutations filter samples metadata lacking mutations .data (flag) show_sample_ids show sample_ids_on_x_axis (flag) interactive plot interactive (boolean) interactive_svg_width dimensions interactive plot (number) interactive_svg_height dimensions interactive plot (number) xlab_title x axis lable. Set xlab_title = NULL remove title (string) ylab_title y axis interactive plot. Set ylab_title = NULL remove title (string) fontsize_xlab size x axis title (number) fontsize_ylab size y axis title (number) fontsize_genes size y axis text (gene names) (number) fontsize_samples size x axis text (sample names). Ignored unless show_sample_ids set true (number) fontsize_count fontsize gene mutation count x axis (number) tile_height proportion available vertical space tile take (0-1) (number) tile_width proportion available horizontal space  tile take (0-1) (number) colour_backround colour used background non-mutated tiles (string) draw_gene_barplot add barplot describing number samples gene mutated (right side) (flag) draw_tmb_barplot add barplot describing total number mutations sample (main plot). single gene mutated multiple times, mutations counted towards total (flag) show_all_samples show samples oncoplot, even mutations selected genes. Samples described metadata mutations still filtered default, can show setting metadata_require_mutations = FALSE  (flag) verbose verbose mode (flag)

title: Generate score based on genes — score_based_on_gene_rank
text: score (higher = higher sorting order) (number)

title: Generate score based on genes — score_based_on_gene_rank
code: if (FALSE) { # First set of genes has a high rank since both BRCA2 and EGFR are mutated score_based_on_gene_rank(c("TERT", "EGFR", "PTEN", "BRCA2"), c("EGFR", "BRCA2"), gene_rank = 1:2)  # If EGFR is mutated without BRCA2, we get a lower score score_based_on_gene_rank(c("TERT", "EGFR", "PTEN", "IDH1"), c("EGFR", "BRCA2"), gene_rank = 1:2)  # If BRCA2 is mutated without EGFR, # we get a score lower than BRCA2+EGFR but higher than EGFR alone due to higher gene_rank of BRCA2 score_based_on_gene_rank(c("TERT", "IDH1", "PTEN", "BRCA2"), c("EGFR", "BRCA2"), gene_rank = 1:2) }
